## PROJECT DOCUMENTATION: NUTRIAI
System Architecture & Product Specifications

Target Recipient: Corporate Technical Review Committee / Enterprise Stakeholders

1. Executive Summary
NutriAI is an advanced, high-performance intelligent health and nutrition ecosystem engineered to optimize personal wellness through algorithmic 
data models, image recognition, and conversational artificial intelligence. The platform bridges the gap between passive health monitoring and
proactive dynamic interventions, delivering continuous real-time nutritional tracking, predictive data-driven dietary insights, hyper-localized 
health optimization, and immediate meal substitutions.

2. Core Architectural Features & Functional Design
### A. Dynamic Intelligent Goal Modeling
Variable Goal Alignment: The system features a customizable user configuration matrix enabling precise adjustments for targeted somatic 
objectives, specifically optimized for weight gain acceleration or weight loss mitigation profiles.  Macro & Caloric Scaling: Caloric ceilings 
and foundational macronutrient splits (Protein, Carbohydrates, and Fats) adapt dynamically in response to user inputs and verified logging 
behaviors. 

### B. Computer Vision Food Identification System
High-Confidence Feature Extraction: Integrated image analysis allows users to scan food items instantly via camera or file uploads. The 
deep-learning subsystem calculates nutrition profiles based on estimated serving sizes. 
Automated Quality & Classification Filtering: The system reads confidence scores and evaluates nutritional indexes. It features an automated 
safety trigger that performs a logical detour based on food classification criteria:  The AI Coach Activation Rule: If the system detects a 
nutritional score below 7.5, or if the scanning model detects an item categorized as non-food, the user interface halts traditional logging 
and directly initiates the specialized AI Coach Mode.  

### C. Conversational GenAI Guidance (Coach Nova)
Instant Context-Aware Response Loop: A conversational micro-agent, "Coach Nova," provides real-time interactions.  
Contextual Insight Aggregation: 
The assistant pulls data from contemporary sleep quality telemetry, biometric stress points, and caloric history to answer natural 
language queries and automatically append suggested recipes directly to the planner.  

### D. Predictive Prescriptive Food Swap Engine
Dynamic Deficit & Swap Optimization: 
When an improper, high-glycemic, or calorically dense meal is identified, the system initiates a substitution sequence. 
Detailed Analytics Compounding: Alternatives are displayed side-by-side with comparative analytics showing reductions in calories/sugars along
with increases in fiber and protein. The interface calculates cumulative weekly savings to encourage user compliance.  

### E. Hyper-Localized Healthy Restaurant Integration
Geo-Fenced Culinary Mapping: Integrates location-based services to detect proximity to vendor partners.  
Curated Health Filters: Users can browse verified healthy restaurants and filter items by specific dietary properties, matching options 
directly to their active fitness goals.  

### F. Comprehensive Historical Ledger & Telemetry
Aggregated Meal Records: Provides an immutable historical data structure tracking consecutive daily meal logs.  
Macro/Caloric Averages: Computes running historical averages alongside total caloric intake to help users track variations over time.  

